# Windows Enumeration - Remote Management Users Group

## Objective

The goal of this task was to:

* Connect to a Windows target system
* Enumerate members of the "Remote Management Users" local group
* Identify a user other than the specified one

---

## Initial Access

Connected to the target system using a Netcat bind shell:

nc 192.168.233.220 4444

This provided a command shell for enumeration.

---

## Enumerating the Remote Management Users Group

Executed the following command:

net localgroup "Remote Management Users"

### Explanation

* net localgroup → displays members of a local group
* "Remote Management Users" → target group name

---

## Observed Output

The command returned the following members:

* daveadmin
* steve

---

## Identifying the Required User

The task required identifying a user other than "steve".

### Result

daveadmin

---

## Key Concept

The "Remote Management Users" group allows users to manage the system remotely using Windows Remote Management (WinRM).

---

## Practical Relevance

If valid credentials are available, remote access can be attempted using tools such as:

evil-winrm -i <target-ip> -u <username> -p <password>

This can provide a remote shell over WinRM.

---

## Summary

* Accessed the target system via Netcat
* Enumerated local group membership
* Identified an additional user in the Remote Management Users group
* Recognized the importance of this group for remote access
